            "html": "<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/0128c0a4ce2195d2b4e1b472e4eebcfe-a6c0e.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; z-index: -1; display: block; \"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 66.66666666666666%;position: relative; width: 100%; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"jeremy bishop 262119\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/0128c0a4ce2195d2b4e1b472e4eebcfe-83ce8.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/0128c0a4ce2195d2b4e1b472e4eebcfe-14b6a.jpg 185w,\n/static/0128c0a4ce2195d2b4e1b472e4eebcfe-ba333.jpg 370w,\n/static/0128c0a4ce2195d2b4e1b472e4eebcfe-83ce8.jpg 740w,\n/static/0128c0a4ce2195d2b4e1b472e4eebcfe-ce974.jpg 1110w,\n/static/0128c0a4ce2195d2b4e1b472e4eebcfe-bfd67.jpg 1480w,\n/static/0128c0a4ce2195d2b4e1b472e4eebcfe-86300.jpg 2220w,\n/static/0128c0a4ce2195d2b4e1b472e4eebcfe-a6c0e.jpg 5472w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 740px) 100vw, 740px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    \n<em>Photo by <a href=\"https://unsplash.com/@tidesinourveins\">Jeremy Bishop</a> via <a href=\"https://unsplash.com/?photo=XxpCNQ_w3is\">Unsplash</a></em></p>\n<p>Code blocks are part of the Markdown spec, but syntax highlighting isn‚Äôt.\nHowever, many renderers support syntax highlighting.\nIn <a href=\"https://www.gatsbyjs.org/docs/packages/gatsby-remark-prismjs/\">gatsby-remark-prismjs</a>, we use ü§î <a href=\"http://prismjs.com/\">PrismJS</a>.</p>\n<h2 id=\"inline-code\"><a href=\"#inline-code\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Inline code</h2>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\">\n      <pre class=\"language-no-highlight\"><code>Inline `code` has `back-ticks around` it.</code></pre>\n      </div>\n<p>Inline <code>code</code> has <code>back-ticks around</code> it.</p>\n<h2 id=\"code-blocks\"><a href=\"#code-blocks\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Code blocks</h2>\n<p>In Markdown, blocks of code are either fenced by lines with three back-ticks\n<code>```</code>, or are indented with four spaces. Fenced code\nblocks are easier to write and maintain, and only they support syntax\nhighlighting by indicating a language.</p>\n<p>To see the complete list of supported languages, and how to write language\nnames, see the <a href=\"http://prismjs.com/#languages-list\">PrismJS homepage</a>.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\">\n      <pre class=\"language-none\"><code>```javascript\nvar s = \"JavaScript syntax highlighting\";\nalert(s);\n```\n\n```python\ns = \"Python syntax highlighting\"\nprint s\n```\n\n```\nNo language indicated, so no syntax highlighting.\nBut let's throw in a &lt;b&gt;tag&lt;/b&gt;.\n```</code></pre>\n      </div>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\">\n      <pre class=\"language-javascript\"><code><span class=\"token keyword\">var</span> s <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"JavaScript syntax highlighting\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token function\">alert</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>s<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n</code></pre>\n      </div>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\">\n      <pre class=\"language-python\"><code>s <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"Python syntax highlighting\"</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">print</span> s\n</code></pre>\n      </div>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\">\n      <pre class=\"language-none\"><code>No language indicated, so no syntax highlighting.\nBut let's throw in a <b>tag</b>.</code></pre>\n      </div>\n<h2 id=\"line-highlighting\"><a href=\"#line-highlighting\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Line highlighting</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gatsbyjs.org/docs/packages/gatsby-remark-prismjs/\">gatsby-remark-prismjs</a> has its own line highlighting implementation which\ndiffers a bit from PrismJS‚Äôs own. You can find out everything about it in the\n<a href=\"https://www.gatsbyjs.org/docs/packages/gatsby-remark-prismjs/\">corresponding README</a>.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\">\n      <pre class=\"language-none\"><code>```javascript{1-2,22}\n// In your gatsby-config.js\n// Let's make this line very long so that our container has to scroll its overflow‚Ä¶\nplugins: [\n  {\n    resolve: `gatsby-transformer-remark`,\n    options: {\n      plugins: [\n        {\n          resolve: `gatsby-remark-images`,\n          options: {\n            maxWidth: 756,\n          },\n        },\n        {\n          resolve: `gatsby-remark-responsive-iframe`,\n          options: {\n            wrapperStyle: `margin-bottom: 1.0725rem`,\n          },\n        },\n        `gatsby-remark-copy-linked-files`,\n        `gatsby-remark-smartypants`,\n        `gatsby-remark-prismjs`,\n      ]\n    }\n  }\n]\n```</code></pre>\n      </div>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\">\n      <pre class=\"language-javascript\"><code><span class=\"gatsby-highlight-code-line\"><span class=\"token comment\" spellcheck=\"true\">// In your gatsby-config.js</span>\n</span><span class=\"gatsby-highlight-code-line\"><span class=\"token comment\" spellcheck=\"true\">// Let's make this line very long so that our container has to scroll its overflow‚Ä¶</span>\n</span>plugins<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    resolve<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token template-string\"><span class=\"token string\">`gatsby-transformer-remark`</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n    options<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n      plugins<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span>\n        <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n          resolve<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token template-string\"><span class=\"token string\">`gatsby-remark-images`</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n          options<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n            maxWidth<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token number\">756</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n          <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n        <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n        <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n          resolve<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token template-string\"><span class=\"token string\">`gatsby-remark-responsive-iframe`</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n          options<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n            wrapperStyle<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token template-string\"><span class=\"token string\">`margin-bottom: 1.0725rem`</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n          <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n        <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n        <span class=\"token template-string\"><span class=\"token string\">`gatsby-remark-copy-linked-files`</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n        <span class=\"token template-string\"><span class=\"token string\">`gatsby-remark-smartypants`</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n<span class=\"gatsby-highlight-code-line\">        <span class=\"token template-string\"><span class=\"token string\">`gatsby-remark-prismjs`</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n</span>      <span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span>\n</code></pre>\n      </div>\n<p>Let‚Äôs do something crazy and add a list with another code example:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>A list item</strong></p>\n<p>‚Ä¶and a paragraph! In my younger and more vulnerable years my father gave me some advice that I‚Äôve been turning over in my mind ever since.</p>\n<ol>\n<li>A nested numbered list</li>\n<li>‚ÄúWhenever you feel like criticizing any one,‚Äù he told me, ‚Äújust remember that all the people in this world haven‚Äôt had the advantages that you‚Äôve had.‚Äù</li>\n</ol>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Roger that, now back to topic: <em>Highlighted code blocks work here, too:</em></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\">\n      <pre class=\"language-css\"><code><span class=\"token selector\">.clearfix:after</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n\t<span class=\"token property\">visibility</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> hidden<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\t<span class=\"token property\">display</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> block<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\t<span class=\"token property\">font-size</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> 0<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\t<span class=\"token property\">content</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\" \"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\t<span class=\"token property\">clear</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> both<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\t<span class=\"token property\">height</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> 0<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\t<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token selector\">.clearfix</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> <span class=\"token property\">display</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> inline-table<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"gatsby-highlight-code-line\"><span class=\"token comment\" spellcheck=\"true\">/* Hides from IE-mac \\*/</span>\n</span><span class=\"token selector\">* html .clearfix</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> <span class=\"token property\">height</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> 1%<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token selector\">.clearfix</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> <span class=\"token property\">display</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> block<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"gatsby-highlight-code-line\"><span class=\"token comment\" spellcheck=\"true\">/* End hide from IE-mac */</span>\n</span></code></pre>\n      </div>\n<p>Wow, ‚ÄúIE-mac‚Äù? <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Internet_Explorer_for_Mac\">Yeah, that was a thing</a> back in the day ‚Ä¶ a good one at the time, too:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Initial versions were developed from the same code base as Internet Explorer for Windows. Later versions diverged, particularly with the release of version 5 which included the cutting edge, <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fault-tolerant\">fault-tolerant</a> and highly standards-compliant <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tasman_(layout_engine)\">Tasman</a> <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Layout_engine\">layout engine</a>.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Source: <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Internet_Explorer_for_Mac\">https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Internet<em>Explorer</em>for_Mac</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>** The last list item** ‚Äì- no more list items after this one, pinky swear!</p>\n</li>\n</ul>",
